text: Acleris aestuosa is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in Japan (Shikoku).Acleris at funet The wingspan is 18–21 mm.Japanese Moths The larvae feed on Fagus crenata.Tortricidae Food Plant Database ==References== Category:Moths described in 1965 aestuosa Category:Moths of Japan
